AGI -&nbsp; It is in stable conditions although critical the policeman Christian Di Martino, attacked and stabbed to the back in the night at the Lambrate station in Milan. The 35-year-old deputy inspector was operated in the night at the Niguarda hospital to contain the bleeding caused by the three phendents in the back. Doctors have not yet dissolved prognosis.
&nbsp;
The Moroccan man arrested to have seriously injured a police officer is called Hasan Hamis and, as reported by the police officer, has several aliases in databases and previous iterations against heritage and resistance to official public.
<h2> The story
Around midnight last, this reconstruction, the Railway Police requested the intervention of the policemen of the Police of the Police of Milan for the presence of a man in a strong state of agitation who, while he was near the railways in the station, was throwing stones against trains and people and had hit the head a woman, Italian of 55 years, then transported in green code at the hospital Fatebenefratelli.
&nbsp;
Two patrols arrived and the man, "in evidently altered and uncooperative psychic state", was hit with the taser, "without however that the discharge was effective because of the jacket that the same one wore".
&nbsp;
A colluctation was born and the 37-year-old struck with three back defenders the 35-year-old Deputy Inspector of the State Police with three back defenders. The attacker is now at the San Vittore prison.

