AGI - The special currency police core of the Guardia di Finanza has seized approximately 130 million euros to two pro-tempore components of the cda of the airline Itavia. The decree was issued by the gip of Milan, at the request of the prosecutor of Milan.<br> According to the investigations, the two directors, who obtained the control of the management of the society, becoming also the majority shareholders, "they would almost have eliminated the residual corporate patrimony deriving from the compensations paid to the society from the ministries of Defense and the Infrastructures and the Transports, following the massacre of Ubstica of particular 1980".
&nbsp;
The financing from 130 million euros would have been used by the two councillors of the cda - according to the investigations coordinated by the Albertini pm - also to extinguish the bank loan used precisely to acquire the majority package in Itavia thus strengthening their position within the same. The corporate operations "have already been the subject - reports in a note the prosecutor Marcello Viola - of censorship by the civil judiciary which, in April 2023, had appointed a special curator who, since May 2023 evidenced the irregularity of the two financing operations > in damage of the society, of minority members and creditors. In light of what is highlighted by the special curator, the protection of the heritage of society was entrusted to a judicial administrator." From the investigations of the financiers it emerged as the sums, deriving from the financing of 130 million euros provided by Itavia, have been reused for foreign purposes to the concession of the credit line. The two former directors, the former liquidator and the mayors are investigated, the latter for failing any control over conflict situations of interest and not adopting the measures required by law to prevent alleged illicit financial transactions.

